1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,557
AI gives answers. Alpha Gym trains judgment.

2
00:00:09,557 --> 00:00:23,891
Replay, decide, reveal, and review: the user stays responsible for the judgment.

3
00:00:23,891 --> 00:00:37,032
The home page frames the app as a decision hall, not another generic dashboard.

4
00:00:37,032 --> 00:00:52,561
Users practice on past snapshots without future leakage, then reveal the true outcome.

5
00:00:52,561 --> 00:01:08,091
A fixed hover inspector keeps daily OHLC and indicators above the chart.

6
00:01:08,091 --> 00:01:22,425
Fundamentals include valuation and quality signals instead of one long paragraph.

7
00:01:22,425 --> 00:01:39,149
GPT is used for AI summaries, debate, judge scoring, and personalized coaching.

8
00:01:39,149 --> 00:01:54,679
The coach critiques the submitted reasoning, not a canned template.

9
00:01:54,679 --> 00:02:09,014
Live analysis uses the same workbench, then records entry price, time, side, and rationale.

10
00:02:09,014 --> 00:02:23,349
The app separates live portfolio decisions from historical practice answers.

11
00:02:23,349 --> 00:02:37,683
Codex built the full stack; GPT-5.6 powers the AI path through structured JSON.

12
00:02:37,683 --> 00:02:47,240
GitHub: github.com/houyehh/FinDebate

